content.description: Start on the far right of the horizontal crack, traverse left then up the arÃªte. Top out at the apex.

Pretty awesome climb, but I am sure someone has done it before. 

  Climb the slabby face right of the backside of the boulder. Use anything left of the big crack on the right side (including arete up top), and anything right of the crack on the left. Make your way up the face using good holds till you reach the top. Only problem is that it is super dirty. Could use some cleaning!
content.location: Walk to the right from the backside of the boulder. The face is right there!

content.description: Traverse the entire boulder avoiding the lip till the last move. Crux comes after squeezing past the big tree. Fun little crimps!
content.location: Sit start at crack on left side traverse right, finish where Plutocrat tops out.

content.description: sit start on far left of boulder.  make move into the "flying saucer" type sloper/jug thing.  Probably the coolest hold I've ever grabbed.  Then its a very casual traverse across the lip on jugs to the end.  be careful for potential holds to break along top.
content.location: just before the Godfather block on the right.  traverse is on the opposite side of godfather block.

content.description:
Start with right hand low on the right side of the arete, left hand on a cool iron crimp. Slap your way up the arete and top out directly. 

  Short but has some fun moves.
content.location: The arete right of Zoro's Conundrum

content.description: Climb up the backside of boulder using horizontal cracks and large ledge for feet.  Corner is optional for a little diversity.  I think this often gets forgotten about.
content.location: Backside of boulder facing the Godfather boulder.

content.description:
Large boulder with obvious, unique crack lines. 

  Please let me know if this boulder is posted elsewhere on MP--it's so obvious I'm sure it's not new to Gov Dodge climbers, but we couldn't find it on the site so figured we'd put it up.
